<p>The function is continuous at $x=a$ if $\lim_{x\to a} f(x)=f(a)$.</p>

<p>For $\lim_{x\to a} f(x)$,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\lim_{x\to 2} (2x^{2}-1) &amp;= 2(2)^2-1 \\
	&amp;= 2(4)-1 \\
	&amp;= 7
\end{align*}\]

<p>And for $f(a)$,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	f(2) &amp;= 2(2)^{2}-1 \\
	&amp;= 7
\end{align*}\]

<p>Since $\lim_{x\to 2} f(x)=f(2)$, the function is <strong>continuous</strong>.</p>

